<nav class="nav" id="nav" data-screen-label="Nav"><svg class="sunmark" viewBox="0 0 32 32" aria-hidden="true"><circle class="sun-disc" cx="16" cy="16" r="10"></circle></svg><a class="wm" href="/">AMPM <small>BUILDING SERVICES</small></a><div class="links"><a href="/services/" class="">Services</a><a href="/work/" class="">Work</a><a href="/compliance/" class="">Compliance</a><a href="/about/" class="">About</a><a href="/contact/" class="">Contact</a></div><a class="phone" href="tel:03300430080">0330 043 0080</a></nav><div class="page" style="--svc: var(--m-green);"><div class="shell"><section class="sec p-hero"><div class="reveal in"><span class="svc-bar" style="background: var(--m-green);"></span></div><div class="reveal in"><div class="kicker">Services · 01</div></div><h1 class="reveal d1 in">Mechanical, Electrical &amp; Public Health</h1><p class="lede reveal d2 in">Mechanical &amp; Electrical is the engine of the business — and the line most clients lead with. We self-deliver the full MEPH scope, from plant and distribution to public health and structured data, so the most technical package on a job sits with <strong>one accountable team.</strong></p><div class="reveal d3 in" style="margin-top: 28px;"><a class="btn line sm" href="/contact/">Enquire about MEPH →</a></div></section><section class="sec tight"><div class="reveal in" style="margin-bottom: 32px;"><div class="kicker">What we deliver</div><h2 class="dhead sm">The full MEPH scope,<br>self-delivered.</h2></div><div class="capgroups reveal in"><div class="capgroup"><h4><span class="dot" style="background: var(--m-green);"></span><span>Mechanical &amp; HVAC</span></h4><ul><li>Heating &amp; cooling systems</li><li>Ventilation &amp; air handling</li><li>Heat pumps &amp; low-carbon plant</li><li>Pipework &amp; plant rooms</li><li>Commissioning &amp; handover</li></ul></div><div class="capgroup"><h4><span class="dot" style="background: var(--m-green);"></span><span>Electrical</span></h4><ul><li>1st &amp; 2nd fix</li><li>Distribution boards &amp; switchgear</li><li>EV charging infrastructure</li><li>Lighting &amp; power</li><li>Testing &amp; certification (NICEIC)</li></ul></div><div class="capgroup"><h4><span class="dot" style="background: var(--m-green);"></span><span>Public health</span></h4><ul><li>Hot &amp; cold water services</li><li>Above-ground drainage</li><li>Sanitaryware &amp; fit-out</li><li>Water hygiene &amp; compliance</li></ul></div><div class="capgroup"><h4><span class="dot" style="background: var(--m-green);"></span><span>Data &amp; IT infrastructure</span></h4><ul><li>Structured cabling</li><li>Containment &amp; comms rooms</li><li>IT-infrastructure fit</li><li>Resilient power to racks</li></ul></div></div></section><section class="sec tight"><div class="reveal in" style="margin-bottom: 32px;"><div class="kicker">How we work</div><h2 class="dhead sm">From survey to handover —<br>and beyond.</h2></div><ol class="steps reveal in"><li class="step"><span class="step-n">01</span><div><h4>Survey &amp; design</h4><p>We survey the existing services, model the loads and produce a coordinated MEPH design — or develop a consultant’s design through to installation.</p></div></li><li class="step"><span class="step-n">02</span><div><h4>Procure &amp; coordinate</h4><p>Plant, distribution and specialist packages procured early and coordinated with the trades above and below, so the M&amp;E never becomes the programme’s bottleneck.</p></div></li><li class="step"><span class="step-n">03</span><div><h4>Install</h4><p>First and second fix self-delivered by our own engineers, sequenced floor-by-floor around live, occupied buildings where needed.</p></div></li><li class="step"><span class="step-n">04</span><div><h4>Commission &amp; certify</h4><p>Witnessed commissioning to CIBSE and BSRIA codes, full electrical testing to BS 7671, and a complete set of O&amp;M and as-built records.</p></div></li><li class="step"><span class="step-n">05</span><div><h4>Handover &amp; maintain</h4><p>Demonstration, training and a clean handover — then planned maintenance and a 24/7 line if you want us to keep the building running.</p></div></li></ol></section><section class="sec tight"><div class="reveal in" style="margin-bottom: 32px;"><div class="kicker">Standards &amp; compliance</div><h2 class="dhead sm">Built to the codes that<br>matter on handover.</h2></div><div class="capgroups reveal in"><div class="capgroup"><h4><span class="dot" style="background: var(--m-green);"></span><span>The standards we build to</span></h4><ul><li>BS 7671 — IET Wiring Regulations (18th Edition)</li><li>CIBSE &amp; BSRIA commissioning codes</li><li>Building Regulations Parts L, F &amp; P</li><li>HSG274 &amp; BS 8558 — water hygiene &amp; services</li><li>CDM 2015 across every package</li></ul></div><div class="capgroup"><h4><span class="dot" style="background: var(--m-green);"></span><span>Backed by AMPM Group</span></h4><ul><li>The Group’s accreditations behind every job</li><li>29 years of group trading history, since 1997</li><li>One project manager accountable per programme</li><li>Full commissioning, O&amp;M and as-built records</li><li>PQQ and reference packs on request</li></ul></div></div></section><section class="sec tight"><div class="reveal in" style="margin-bottom: 28px;"><div class="kicker">Sectors</div><h2 class="dhead sm">Where MEPH<br>matters most.</h2></div><div class="sectorrow reveal in"><span class="sector">Commercial offices</span><span class="sector">Commercial fit-out</span><span class="sector">Healthcare</span><span class="sector">Education</span><span class="sector">Industrial &amp; logistics</span><span class="sector">Data centres</span><span class="sector">Residential &amp; BTR</span><span class="sector">Hospitality &amp; leisure</span><span class="sector">Public sector</span></div><p class="body" style="margin-top:22px;max-width:60ch;">We deliver MEPH packages across London and the South East — including Sussex, Surrey, Kent, Hampshire and Berkshire — for direct clients, Tier-1 main contractors and blue-chip FM providers.</p></section><section class="sec tight"><div class="intro2 reveal in"><div><div class="kicker">Market drivers</div><h2 class="dhead sm">Where the work<br>is coming from.</h2></div><p class="body">Compliance-led upgrades and M&amp;E packages — coming direct from clients, Tier-1 main contractors and blue-chip FM providers.</p></div></section><section class="sec"><div class="reveal in" style="margin-bottom: 32px;"><div class="kicker">Representative projects</div><h2 class="dhead sm">MEPH work, in the field.</h2></div><div class="caselist reveal in"><div class="case-card"><img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1497366216548-37526070297c?auto=format&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=900&amp;q=75" alt="CASE — MEPH" loading="lazy" style="width: 100%; height: 200px; display: block; object-fit:cover;" /><span class="ctag" style="background: var(--m-green); position: absolute;">MEPH · Cat-B</span><h4>Commercial office — City of London</h4><p class="cs">Full M&amp;E package for a Cat-B fit-out across multiple floors.</p><div class="cm"><div><div class="k">Value</div><div class="v">£2.4m</div></div><div><div class="k">Programme</div><div class="v">26 wks</div></div></div></div><div class="case-card"><img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1592833167665-ebf9d00a4799?auto=format&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=900&amp;q=75" alt="CASE — MEPH" loading="lazy" style="width: 100%; height: 200px; display: block; object-fit:cover;" /><span class="ctag" style="background: var(--m-green); position: absolute;">MEPH · Heat pumps</span><h4>Managed estate — Surrey</h4><p class="cs">Air-source heat-pump retrofit and plant replacement across several blocks.</p><div class="cm"><div><div class="k">Value</div><div class="v">£1.1m</div></div><div><div class="k">Programme</div><div class="v">18 wks</div></div></div></div><div class="case-card"><img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1593941707882-a5bba14938c7?auto=format&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=900&amp;q=75" alt="CASE — MEPH" loading="lazy" style="width: 100%; height: 200px; display: block; object-fit:cover;" /><span class="ctag" style="background: var(--m-green); position: absolute;">MEPH · EV</span><h4>Car park — South East</h4><p class="cs">Multi-bay EV charging installation with distribution-board upgrade.</p><div class="cm"><div><div class="k">Value</div><div class="v">£540k</div></div><div><div class="k">Programme</div><div class="v">12 wks</div></div></div></div></div><p class="case-note">Representative of the MEPH work we are set up to deliver. Named, full-format case studies follow as projects complete — PQQ references available on request.</p></section><section class="sec tight"><div class="reveal in" style="margin-bottom: 28px;"><div class="kicker">FAQs</div><h2 class="dhead sm">MEPH questions,<br>answered.</h2></div><div class="faq reveal in"><details class="faq-item"><summary>What does MEPH stand for?</summary><p>Mechanical, Electrical and Public Health — the three core building-services disciplines. We self-deliver all three as one coordinated package, so the most technical part of a job sits with a single accountable team.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>Do you take on design, or install only?</summary><p>Both. We can develop a consultant’s design through to installation, or design-and-build the M&amp;E package from the brief — including load modelling, coordination and specification.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>Can you work in an occupied or live building?</summary><p>Yes. Much of our work is phased around live buildings — out-of-hours isolations, temporary supplies and floor-by-floor sequencing — so the building keeps running while we install.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>What standards is the work certified to?</summary><p>Electrical installations are designed and tested to BS 7671 (18th Edition); mechanical systems are commissioned to CIBSE and BSRIA codes; and everything is delivered under CDM 2015 with full O&amp;M and as-built documentation.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>Do you cover heat pumps and low-carbon plant?</summary><p>Yes — air-source heat-pump retrofits, low-carbon plant and the electrical-distribution upgrades they need are a growing part of our MEPH work, alongside EV charging and energy-efficiency packages.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>Which areas do you cover?</summary><p>We deliver MEPH packages across London and the South East, including Sussex, Surrey, Kent, Hampshire and Berkshire. Send us the site address and we’ll arrange a survey.</p></details></div></section><section class="sec tight line-top"><div class="reveal in" style="margin-bottom: 24px;"><div class="kicker">The other three lines</div><h2 class="dhead sm">One contractor,<br>four service lines.</h2></div><div class="otherlines reveal in"><div class="otherline"><span class="ol-l"><span class="ol-sw" style="background: var(--m-purple);"></span><span class="ol-nm">Commercial</span></span><span class="ol-go">→</span></div><div class="otherline"><span class="ol-l"><span class="ol-sw" style="background: var(--m-orange);"></span><span class="ol-nm">Fabric</span></span><span class="ol-go">→</span></div><div class="otherline"><span class="ol-l"><span class="ol-sw" style="background: var(--m-blue);"></span><span class="ol-nm">Groundworks</span></span><span class="ol-go">→</span></div></div></section></div><section class="band" data-nav-dark="true" style="background: var(--m-green); color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><div class="shell"><div class="cta-split reveal in"><div><div class="kicker on-dark">Talk to us about MEPH</div><h2 class="dhead sm" style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Scope, programme,<br>stage — send it over.</h2><p class="body" style="color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9); margin-top: 16px;">A named contact, not a sales team, comes back within 24 hours. Include the package, programme and stage if you can.</p></div><div class="cta-row2" style="flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start;"><a class="btn ghost" href="/contact/">Enquire about MEPH →</a><a class="btn ghost" href="/compliance/">Compliance &amp; BSA</a></div></div></div></section></div><script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What does MEPH stand for?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Mechanical, Electrical and Public Health — the three core building-services disciplines. AMPM Building Services self-delivers all three as one coordinated package."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Do you take on design, or install only?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Both. We develop a consultant’s design through to installation, or design-and-build the M&E package from the brief."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can you work in an occupied or live building?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Much of our work is phased around live buildings with out-of-hours isolations, temporary supplies and floor-by-floor sequencing."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What standards is the work certified to?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Electrical installations to BS 7671 (18th Edition); mechanical systems commissioned to CIBSE and BSRIA codes; delivered under CDM 2015 with full O&M documentation."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Do you cover heat pumps and low-carbon plant?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes — air-source heat-pump retrofits, low-carbon plant, EV charging and the electrical upgrades they need are a growing part of our MEPH work."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Which areas do you cover?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"London and the South East, including Sussex, Surrey, Kent, Hampshire and Berkshire."}}]}</script><footer class="foot" data-nav-dark="true"><div class="foot-inner"><div><div class="fwm">AMPM</div><span class="fmer" aria-hidden="true"><span style="background: var(--m-green);"></span><s